cff-version: 1.2.0
title: HoloWeights
message: >-
  Toy virtual volumetric tiling of neural-network weights backed by mmap, with sparse touch
  patterns for fiddling memory bandwidth curiosity.
abstract: >-
  Personal sandbox packing model bytes into fixed uint8 tiles, mmap files, sparse route sketches,
  and careful caveats—not a turnkey stack and not claiming bench optics unless stated elsewhere.
authors:
  - name: Mprah-Boamey
type: software
keywords:
  - virtual holography
  - holographic inference
  - volumetric inference
  - optical neural networks
  - optical computing
  - memory-mapped weights
  - sparse tile routing
  - LLM inference
  - quantization
repository-code: https://github.com/mprahboamey/holoweights
license: MIT
